---
// SlicedLabs · studio · © 2026 SlicedLabs — Manifesto / About
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base title="Manifesto — SlicedLabs" description="Own your slice. A food · media · marketing company building in public.">
  <section class="wrap" style="max-width:48rem; padding-block:3rem;">
    <p class="mono">the manifesto</p>
    <h1 class="kinetic" style="font-size:clamp(2.4rem,8vw,5rem);"><span class="spectrum-text">Own your slice.</span></h1>

    <p style="font-size:1.25rem; color:var(--muted); margin-top:1.4rem;">
      SlicedLabs is one company: a <strong style="color:var(--ink);">food · media · marketing</strong> brand
      building a real food empire in public — and proving anyone can own their slice by showing exactly how,
      receipts and all.
    </p>

    <h2 style="margin-top:2.5rem;">What "own your slice" means</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--muted);">
      A slice is something you control end to end — your stack, your audience, your income, your time, your supply.
      We own the audience instead of renting attention. We become the landlord instead of renting the lot.
      We source local now and grow our own later. The same move, repeated at every layer.
    </p>

    <h2 style="margin-top:2rem;">The depth behind it</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--muted);">
      This didn't come from nowhere. It's the distilled discipline of the operators and builders we studied for
      years — value creation, lean systems, selling without sleaze, buying back your time, compounding ownership.
      We don't quote the playbooks; we <em>run</em> them, on camera, and let the receipts make the argument.
    </p>

    <h2 style="margin-top:2rem;">The honest line</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--muted);">
      We never claim a future as a present. The homestead and the skills center are where this is going — they
      aren't here yet, and we'll say so every time. <strong style="color:var(--ink);">Trust math, not promises.</strong>
    </p>

    <div style="margin-top:3rem; text-align:center;">
      <hr class="spectrum-rule" style="max-width:10rem; margin:0 auto 1rem;" />
      <p class="mono">build it in public · show the math</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
